Package projects.pqueue.heaps

Class ArrayMinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • projects.pqueue.heaps.ArrayMinHeap<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, MinHeap<T>
    public class ArrayMinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements MinHeap<T>

    ArrayMinHeap is a MinHeap implemented using an internal array. Since heaps are complete binary trees, using contiguous storage to store them is an excellent idea, since with such storage we avoid wasting bytes per null pointer in a linked implementation.

    You must edit this class! To receive any credit for the unit tests related to this class, your implementation must be a contiguous storage implementation based on a linear Collection like an ArrayList or a Vector (but *not* a LinkedList because it's *not* contiguous storage!). or a raw Java array. We provide an array for you to start with, but if you prefer, you can switch it to a Collection as mentioned above.
